### 1. WRONG WAY - This returns a CUSTOM token (won't work with /api/user/profile)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### 2. RIGHT WAY - Get ID token for testing
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/get-test-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

# Copy the "idToken" from the response above, then use it below

### 3. Test user profile with ID token
GET http://localhost:3000/api/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_YOUR_ID_TOKEN_HERE
